This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category as it proposes a distributed recurrent neural network architecture for fault detection in sensor networks. It also involves learning spatio-temporal correlations between different sensors, which is a common task in neural network research. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. 

Distributed computing is a key aspect of the proposed approach, which could place the paper in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. 

The paper also deals with system-level issues related to sensor networks, such as monitoring the quality of gathered data, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. 

Finally, the paper involves data analysis and processing, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category.
